JOHANNESBURG – Award-winning rapper and business mogul Sean 'Diddy' Combs will be touring Africa soon, with his first stop being Nigeria. It is not yet known when Combs, who has been known by various stages names including Puff Daddy, Puffy, P Diddy, Diddy, Brother Love and Love, will perform on the continent and whether South Africa will be included on his itinerary. The announcement was posted in a video on his Instagram account. @dreamcatchersda my Angels gave my brother @diddy a tee and this is what he had to say about it . --♥️-------------- #Africa #Nigeria A post shared by  Naomi Campbell (@iamnaomicampbell) on The artist also said he would visit Kenya, Senegal and Ivory Coast. Combs has won three Grammy Awards and two MTV Video Music Awards. In 2018, Forbes estimated his net worth at $825-million, making him the second-richest hip-hop artist in the US, behind Jay-Z. - African News Agency